cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CC 

This paper deals with index coding, which is a problem in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of directed graphs to represent the index-coding problems, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper proposes algorithms and techniques to solve the index-coding problem, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
